  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Driver Chauffeur",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will chauffeur the Director, family, colleagues, clients, and guests safely to various locations within Singapore while maintaining the vehicle and assisting with administrative tasks as needed.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive the Director, family, colleagues, clients, and guests to and from locations across Singapore, ensuring timely and safe transportation</li><li>Perform daily vehicle cleaning and wiping to maintain cleanliness and appearance</li><li>Conduct regular car washes and refuel the vehicle to ensure readiness for use</li><li>Monitor and report on vehicle service and maintenance schedules to prevent breakdowns</li><li>Use mobile navigation tools such as Google Maps and Waze to plan efficient routes and avoid delays</li><li>Communicate basic information effectively in English and Mandarin to support coordination during trips</li><li>Assist with administrative duties as requested to support office operations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a valid Class 3 driving license with a good driving record</li><li>Demonstrate at least 5 years of local driving experience, including driving luxury MPVs</li><li>Possess thorough knowledge of Singapore roads and landmarks</li><li>Be willing to work overtime hours, including weekends and public holidays, as needed</li><li>Punctuality is of utmost importance</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Exhibit good interpersonal skills and a responsible, reliable attitude to maintain positive working relationships</li><li>Only Singaporeans need apply</li></ul><p>Working Hours:</p><ul><li>Monday to Friday, 10am to 7pm</li><li>Saturday, half day</li></ul>",
